Runaway corruption will ruin the legacy of President Uhuru Kenyatta, Suna West MP Peter Masara has said. Masara said graft was derailing service delivery. He challenged Uhuru to borrow a leaf from Tanzanian President Pombe Magufuli in the fight against graft. "Uhuru's Big Four agenda will be swallowed by corruption if he is not careful," Masara said. He was speaking on Saturday in Migori during the launch of mentorship for KCSE candidates at the Kenya Relief Academy. Click here for the latest political news  